            <div class="col-4 col-12-medium">
              <section class="highlight">
                <h3><a href="#">Who Can Apply?</a></h3>
                <p class="eligibility-text"></p>
                <p>
                  Eligible applicants must meet several specific criteria to participate in this exchange program. They
                  must be currently enrolled as full-time students at a Jamaican university, working toward a 4-year
                  Bachelor of Science (BSc) degree, and maintain at least a 2.0 GPA. Beyond academic requirements,
                  students must independently find and secure acceptance with an approved program sponsor organization.
                  Additionally, they must demonstrate adequate English language skills, obtain valid health insurance
                  coverage for their time abroad, and complete all necessary paperwork and documentation required for
                  the exchange program.
                </p>
                <ul class="actions">
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://j1visa.state.gov/programs/" target="_blank" class="btn-standard btn-primary">Learn More</a>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </section>
            </div>

            <div class="col-4 col-12-medium">
              <section class="highlight">
                <h3><a>Local Agencies</a></h3>
                <p>
                  Local Jamaican agencies serve as on-the-ground facilitators that help Jamaican students and
                  professionals seeking to participate in the U.S. exchange program. These agencies provide
                  comprehensive support by identifying and connecting applicants with approved U.S. program sponsors,
                  assisting with job applications and placement processes, guiding participants through visa application
                  and processing procedures, and ensuring all candidates meet the necessary program eligibility
                  requirements before departure. Essentially, they act as local intermediaries that streamline the
                  entire application process, making it easier for Jamaican participants to navigate the complex
                  requirements of U.S. exchange programs while providing personalized, in-country support throughout the
                  process.
                </p>
                <ul class="actions">
                  <li>
                    <a href="https://j1visa.state.gov/sponsors/" target="_blank" class="btn-standard btn-primary">Learn More</a>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </section>
            </div>

            <div class="col-4 col-12-medium">
              <section class="highlight">
                <h3><a>Sponsors</a></h3>
                <p>
                  Designated sponsors are authorized organizations that act as intermediaries in U.S. exchange programs,
                  serving three key functions: they match international students and participants with approved U.S.
                  host employers or organizations, ensure that both participants and hosts comply with all U.S.
                  Department of State regulations and program requirements, and provide ongoing guidance and support
                  throughout the participant's entire exchange experience. Essentially, they serve as the official
                  oversight body that facilitates exchange programs while maintaining government standards and
                  participant welfare.
                </p>
                <ul class="actions">
                  <li>
                    <a
